**Formula 1: Drive to Survive Season 7**

The seventh season of the critically acclaimed documentary series [Formula 1: Drive to Survive](/Formula_1:_Drive_to_Survive) delves into the tumultuous and exhilarating [2024 Formula One World Championship](/2024_Formula_One_World_Championship). This installment, comprising 10 episodes, premiered on [Netflix](/Netflix) on 7 March 2025, offering an unfiltered, behind-the-scenes look at the drivers, teams, and the sheer drama that defines the pinnacle of motorsport. It’s not just about the races; it’s about the human element, the relentless pressure, and the often-unseen machinations that dictate the fate of a championship.

**Premise and Release**

The season made its debut on 7 March 2025, a date circled with anticipation by fans who have come to expect the gripping narrative style that has become synonymous with [Formula 1: Drive to Survive](/Formula_1:_Drive_to_Survive). This seventh season meticulously documents the key events and unfolding storylines of the [2024](/2024_Formula_One_World_Championship) season. It captures the seismic shockwaves sent through the sport by [Lewis Hamilton](/Lewis_Hamilton)'s unexpected transfer to [Scuderia Ferrari](/Scuderia_Ferrari), a move that reshaped the driver market and ignited fervent speculation. The season also unflinchingly examines the controversies that swirled around [Christian Horner](/Christian_Horner), exploring the intense scrutiny and its impact on the [Red Bull Racing](/Red_Bull_Racing) team. Furthermore, it chronicles [Lando Norris](/Lando_Norris)'s determined pursuit of a championship title, highlighting his resilience and the McLaren team's resurgence. The narrative arc also includes the poignant farewell of [Daniel Ricciardo](/Daniel_Ricciardo) from Formula One, marking the end of an era for a driver beloved by many. The series, as always, aims to provide context and emotional depth to the on-track action, making the sport accessible and compelling even to those less familiar with its intricacies.

